people who work there have a wider outlook than in the average room.

58:19.000 --> 58:28.000
So, appearance, low voice, connection with abroad, education.

58:28.000 --> 58:32.000
These are the factors that allow you to quickly gain influence.

58:32.000 --> 58:37.000
A very good tool is also getting to know important people.

58:37.000 --> 58:40.000
That is, a certain reflected charisma.

58:40.000 --> 58:45.000
If a person is familiar with showmen, with influential politicians,

58:45.000 --> 58:49.000
in principle, with any person who is more or less famous and is popular,

58:49.000 --> 58:52.000
this will naturally add charisma to him.

58:53.000 --> 58:58.000
In the same list, acquaintance with well-known entrepreneurs

58:58.000 --> 59:01.000
or with unknown but rich entrepreneurs.

59:01.000 --> 59:05.000
Although the acquaintance can be very capricious.

59:07.000 --> 59:09.000
These are all fast resources.

59:09.000 --> 59:14.000
Fast resources are characterized by the fact that they work instantly,

59:14.000 --> 59:20.000
but, unfortunately or fortunately, their action ends quite quickly.

59:21.000 --> 59:24.000
As soon as people begin to communicate more closely with each other,

59:24.000 --> 59:27.000
interact on business,

59:27.000 --> 59:32.000
that is, it is important for us that this interaction is intense and on business,

59:32.000 --> 59:36.000
then fast factors immediately begin to lose their strength.

59:36.000 --> 59:39.000
It is no longer so important whether a person is tall or short,

59:39.000 --> 59:42.000
whether he has a low voice or a high one,

59:42.000 --> 59:45.000
whether he has awards and prizes or not.

59:46.000 --> 59:50.000
Whether he has been abroad 10 times in the last year or only once in Egypt.

59:50.000 --> 59:56.000
This is no longer important, because the qualities that allow him

59:56.000 --> 01:00:04.000
or do not allow him to carry out the functions that we expect from the leader come to the fore.

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:08.000
Let me remind you, these are the four main functions.

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:15.000
Protect, extract, judge, distribute and direct.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:19.000
All the factors that we listed in the fast zone,

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:25.000
they are also such only because they allow us to assume

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:32.000
that their carrier will perform these four functions better than anyone else.

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.000
When we begin to interact with a person,

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:41.000
we begin to understand how much in reality he is able to perform these functions,

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:45.000
how much he is really able to protect us,

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:49.000
how much he is really able to provide us with resources,

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:54.000
how much he is really and correctly able to choose the direction where we should go,

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:59.000
what to strive for, and how fairly he is able to judge and award.

01:00:59.000 --> 01:01:03.000
If a person with these functions does not cope well,

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:12.000
then gradually the target audience will refuse this person the right to manage himself at the social level.

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:16.000
Of course, he will have such tools as coercion,

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:21.000
but he will have such a tool as material influence.

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:28.000
He can fine, issue bonuses, set sales interest,

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:37.000
he can deprive of vacation or, on the contrary, award bonus.

01:01:37.000 --> 01:01:40.000
No one can cancel such tools.

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:42.000
But the ability to simply say,

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:47.000
guys, let's do it so that people really get up and do it,

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:49.000
such a person will no longer exist.

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:53.000
Accordingly, we refer to the long-term factors,

01:01:53.000 --> 01:02:00.000
we refer to the factors that allow in the long term to constantly, every day,

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:04.000
to carry out the four main functions of the leader,

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:07.000
to protect, to extract, to direct and to distribute.

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:09.000
What is needed for this?

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:10.000
It is quite obvious.

01:02:11.000 --> 01:02:14.000
First of all, of course, professional competence is needed for this.

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:18.000
Moreover, if we talk about top managers,

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:21.000
then this competence is not in the specialty.

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:25.000
Here, a top manager may not be a professional.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.000
He must have an idea, but no more,

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:31.000
so as not to interfere with the specialists doing their job.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:34.000
And he must be a professional as a manager.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:37.000
He must understand how social systems function,

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:39.000
what groups are,

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:44.000
what stages of their dynamics they go through

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:48.000
before turning into a really effective unit.

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:54.000
How to turn a working group into a team?

01:02:55.000 --> 01:02:56.000
How?

01:02:57.000 --> 01:03:00.000
He will need a lot of knowledge of psychology

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:03.000
to understand what is happening between people

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:06.000
and what exactly needs to be influenced

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:10.000
to avoid conflicts and to get an effective job.

01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:19.000
Of course, such a factor as the ability to communicate,

01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:23.000
the ability to communicate is necessary for such a leader on a permanent basis.

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:31.000
Because he will need to constantly have the ability to express his thoughts,

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:35.000
to be able to organize discussions correctly,

01:03:35.000 --> 01:03:38.000
to moderate this discussion properly.

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:42.000
All this requires a good communication skill.

01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:48.000
As a result, it is worth noting that working on your communication,

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:53.000
on your ability to communicate well,

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:56.000
is a very important tool,

01:03:56.000 --> 01:04:00.000
because it works as a fast tool and as a long-term tool.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:04.000
And the third thing is that this person should really behave like a leader,

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:07.000
to follow certain behavioral orders,

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:11.000
which will be associated with the image of a charismatic leader,

01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:16.000
with the image of a father, and will not contradict him.

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:20.000
Well, today we have already talked a lot about

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:23.000
what is important to do as a leader.

01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:27.000
Some behavioral rules need to be followed.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:31.000
It's time to analyze this issue a little more in detail.

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:39.000
So, what is the basis for the ability of a leader to manage his target audience?

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:47.000
It is based on the fact that people who follow this leader trust him.

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:53.000
The first and most important quality in the relationship system

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:57.000
that arises between the leader and his accomplices is trust.

01:04:57.000 --> 01:05:00.000
Accomplices must trust their leader,

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:03.000
and the leader must trust his accomplices.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:11.000
Only then will the first ones listen to their leader without any doubts,

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:15.000
and only then will the leader be able to really rely on them,

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:18.000
to count on them doing what he wants from them.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.000
So, the most important category that should exist

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:25.000
in the relationship between the leader and his accomplices is trust.

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:33.000
Therefore, the behavior that the leader should adhere to

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:38.000
should not contradict, but at most strengthen this quality.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:41.000
That is, he should behave in such a way

01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:45.000
that the degree of trust in him increases.

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:49.000
A fairly simple rule follows from here.

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:51.000
Rule number one.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:56.000
The leader must be an absolutely obligatory person.

01:05:57.000 --> 01:05:59.000
He said, he did.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:05.000
That is, he must, firstly, be able to make promises,

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:09.000
take responsibility for them, and, secondly,

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:12.000
if he has already taken the lead, then he does not say that he is not going.

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:15.000
He said, he did.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:20.000
Of course, it is impossible to always keep all your promises.

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:24.000
In such cases, the leader must, again,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:28.000
not let people be in the unknown.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:32.000
At the moment when it becomes clear that it is impossible to keep promises,

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:36.000
the leader must approach his people absolutely honestly and openly

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:40.000
and tell them that this promise will not be fulfilled,

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:43.000
but, for example, some other promise will be fulfilled.

01:06:43.000 --> 01:06:48.000
Thus, we come to the next category, the category of openness.

01:06:49.000 --> 01:06:55.000
Of course, openness can only be allowed by a really strong leader.

01:06:55.000 --> 01:06:57.000
Why?

01:06:57.000 --> 01:07:01.000
Because when the leader opens up completely,

01:07:01.000 --> 01:07:04.000
he thus makes himself more predictable,

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:08.000
more understandable for his target audience,

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:11.000
so that what happens with social distance?

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:14.000
It decreases.

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:18.000
That is, if the reformation is not very strong in terms of significant factors,

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:22.000
then such a leader risks to fall into the trap.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:27.000
Therefore, with openness, the leader must be very careful,

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:29.000
not to overdo it.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:34.000
It is necessary to clearly understand how strong the advantage is in front of the target audience.

01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:41.000
And, by the way, for those leaders who have very strong significant signs,

01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:46.000
so much so that they risk that the separation,

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:49.000
even in the positive direction of increasing social distance,

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:52.000
can throw them into the zone of strangers,

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:56.000
I advise such leaders, on the contrary, to show as much openness as possible,

01:07:56.000 --> 01:08:01.000
maybe even to engage in personal interaction with their subordinates.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.000
To drink beer in the evening,

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:06.000
just to talk about the soul,

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:08.000
to ask about the soul once again,

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:10.000
to ask like a family,

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:13.000
that is, to create additional approximating factors,

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:16.000
so as not to fly out of the zone of a stranger.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:19.000
That is, openness is a tool

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:22.000
with which you can additionally adjust the social distance

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:25.000
between the leader and his target audience.

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:29.000
But obligation is a tough and absolute requirement.

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:34.000
If every fulfilled promise adds trust,

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:39.000
every unfulfilled promise is five times stronger,

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:41.000
it kills trust.

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:43.000
It is enough to do it only a few times.

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:46.000
No matter how high the level of trust in the leader is,

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:49.000
it is enough to fail to fulfill your promises several times in a row,

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:57.000
and the ability to influence people through positive social motivation disappears.

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:03.000
The leader cannot afford to be unnecessary.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:09.000
That is why, for example, when I am called a charismatic leader of showmen,

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:11.000
I am slightly disturbed.

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:17.000
Because publicity, fame, of course, is a good significant factor.

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:21.000
Publicly famous people, of course, have a wide circle of acquaintances.

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:26.000
They are popular, they have a wide access to information.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:29.000
But it is not a fact that they use this information properly.

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:33.000
It is not a fact that they really understand how to do one thing or another.

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:37.000
And it is absolutely not a fact that they know how to keep their word.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:43.000
And by the way, if we are talking about political leaders,

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:48.000
there is nothing worse for a political career of a leader

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:52.000
than to give a public promise, a tough and clear one,

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:56.000
the kind of promise that should be, and then not to keep it.

01:09:56.000 --> 01:10:02.000
That is why, by the way, most of the current politicians avoid giving any clear promises.

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:08.000
The promises they make, the promises they call such, have a vague common character.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:13.000
As a result, it is impossible to understand whether such a promise is kept or not.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:17.000
As a result, they do not risk losing trust.

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:20.000
But they also cannot gain trust in this way.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:27.000
A person who can really give tough, clear promises and keep them for a long time,

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:33.000
instantly, with each next promise, the more significant it is,

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:39.000
the more power and ability to manage the people to whom he gave this promise.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:42.000
Or who know that he made such a promise.

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:49.000
In business, for example, the reputation that my company has,

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:56.000
is largely based on the fact that, for example, we are always tough and clear in financial affairs.

01:10:56.000 --> 01:11:03.000
If we have agreed with our partners that we will pay the agreed terms and conditions,

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:05.000
we will do exactly that.

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:08.000
Because we have a clear and tough rule.

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:15.000
Either we do not agree, or we agree in such a way that we really keep our word.

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:20.000
Moreover, it does not depend on how our partners behave.

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:26.000
They can violate their commitments, but we will fulfill our commitments in any case.

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:31.000
Because it is important not only in relation to these specific agents, as we have behaved,

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:35.000
but for all other people in the market, for all other business community,

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:39.000
it is extremely important to have information that, for example,

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:44.000
Cameo keeps its word and always fulfills its financial obligations.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:47.000
This increases the degree of trust.

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:51.000
As a result, we can communicate with these people and agree on something,

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:54.000
and influence their commercial policies.

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:56.000
And plus, this reduces their financial risks,

01:11:56.000 --> 01:12:00.000
and allows us to get better conditions,

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:03.000
because partners do not need to take risks.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:09.000
So, I will repeat again, because this is extremely important for any charismatic leader of the rule.

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:12.000
The first rule is commitment.

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:16.000
You need to be able to give clear promises,

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:21.000
which have certain deadlines, certain numerical parameters of execution,

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:25.000
so that you can clearly say whether you did it or not.

01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:29.000
And then keep your word, fulfill your obligations on time.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:33.000
The second behavioral rule, which is only two,

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:36.000
everything else is a consequence of the first two.

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:39.000
The second rule I call anti-victim.

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:43.000
So, the second behavioral rule is anti-victim.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:49.000
By this word, I mean a certain combination of behavioral techniques,

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:53.000
behavioral rules, combined with one common thought.

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:57.000
This is the thought of how not to behave.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:13:02.000
Of course, this typology is somewhat conditional.

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:05.000
On the other hand, this is a very good practical tool.

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:11.000
It allows you to easily understand at any time whether you are behaving as a leader should or not.

01:13:11.000 --> 01:13:15.000
So, if you are able to assess your own behavior,

01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:20.000
listen to yourself, see the reflection of your behavior in the eyes of others,

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:25.000
you will be able to constantly correct your behavior in the right direction every minute.

01:13:25.000 --> 01:13:29.000
As a result, the level of trust in you from your target audience,

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:34.000
your people will increase, and the ability to manage them will also increase.

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:36.000
So, anti-victim.

01:13:36.000 --> 01:13:43.000
From the title, it is clear that a leader should behave in the opposite way than a victim.

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:50.000
Let's see how animals or people who become victims behave.

01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:52.000
What do they do?

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:56.000
Well, the first thing is that we talked a lot about the voice today.

